Requirement of service lane on NH 58
Entrance to Ansal Town is about 200 mtrs from Modipuram bypass crossing on the right hand side of the road One has to drive on the wrong side of the road to reach Ansal Town Gate. If one is complying the traffic rule of driving on the left lane one will have to go about 2 to 2.5 km on the left lane before cut in the divider is found to take a U turn and come back to Ansal Town gate. That is 4 km of extra driving. It is recommended and requested that a service lane is constructed on the right hand lane so visitors and residents do not have to drive on the wrong side of the road to enter Ansal Town and avoid possibility of an accident. BTW there have been more than two collisions to my knowledge in the last 3 years.

created_at:
Subject : Repairing of Road and Street Lights.

Respected Sir,

I wish to draw your attention towards the poor maintenance of roads and lights in our locality.

The roads in our locality have not been repaired for a long time. There are pits and ditches on the roads everywhere. The condition of the road becomes all the worst during the rainy season. They cause road accident. At night people sometimes stumble down. Moreover, these pits provide breeding ground for the mosquitoes. Thus there is an outbreak of mosquitoes in the locality leading to the spread of malaria.

Besides, most of the street lights in our locality are out of order. Only a few street lights are functioning. It is darkness in the locality. It has caused a spurt in the incidence of crime in the area. 

I, therefore, request you to kindly take necessary action to mend the ways so that people of the area have good roads and street lights. Hope for early action.

Thanking you 
Your Faithfully 
Ashish kumar verma
593/6 Subhash Nagar Lane no.8 , Meerut 
Contact : 9897905820
description: Repairing of Road and Street Lights
location: Mohan Puri Rd, Police Lines, Meerut, Uttar Pradesh 250003, India
